---
import BaseHead from '../../../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Header from '../../../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../../../components/Footer.astro';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead
			title="Stack Overflow Monitoring — Low Hanging Data"
			description="A data pipeline tracking technology adoption trends from Stack Overflow data, the Developer Survey, PyPI stats, and the dbt Hub registry."
		/>
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />

		<main id="main-content">

			<!-- ─── Hero ──────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
			<div class="project-hero">
				<nav class="breadcrumb" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
					<a href="/projects/">Projects</a>
					<span aria-hidden="true">/</span>
					<span>Stack Overflow Monitoring</span>
				</nav>
				<p class="hero-label">Open Source · Trends</p>
				<h1 class="hero-title">Stack Overflow Monitoring</h1>
				<p class="hero-summary">A data pipeline that tracks technology adoption trends by joining Stack Overflow's public data dump, the annual Developer Survey, PyPI download stats, and the dbt Hub registry.</p>
				<div class="hero-meta">
					<span class="tech-tag">Python</span>
					<span class="tech-tag">click</span>
					<span class="tech-tag">rich</span>
					<span class="tech-tag">pandas</span>
					<span class="meta-sep" aria-hidden="true">·</span>
					<a href="https://github.com/mryagerr/stackoverflow-monitoring" class="repo-link" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">mryagerr/stackoverflow-monitoring ↗</a>
				</div>
			</div>

			<div class="content">

				<!-- ─── Problem ────────────────────────────────────────── -->
				<section class="content-section">
					<h2>The problem</h2>
					<p>
						Most "what's hot in data" lists are vendor-driven or vibes-driven. They reflect
						whoever has a marketing budget, not what engineers actually use or want to learn.
						The signal-to-noise ratio on technology trend reporting is low enough that it is
						nearly useless for any decision that involves real money — hiring, tooling investment,
						training time.
					</p>
					<p>
						This project replaces that noise with a reproducible signal built from public, free,
						primary sources. The inputs are the same data everyone ignores because joining them
						takes an afternoon.
					</p>
				</section>

				<!-- ─── What it produces ───────────────────────────────── -->
				<section class="content-section">
					<h2>What it produces</h2>

					<h3>The Hype Gap report</h3>
					<p>
						The flagship output is a ranked table of technologies sorted by the delta between
						"want to learn" and "used professionally" responses in the Stack Overflow Developer
						Survey. A positive gap means engineers want it but companies have not adopted it.
						A negative gap — the regret index — means it is widely used in production but
						nobody would choose it if they had a vote. Both directions are useful.
					</p>

					<h3>Signals tracked</h3>
					<table class="signals-table">
						<thead>
							<tr>
								<th>Signal</th>
								<th>Source</th>
								<th>Insight</th>
							</tr>
						</thead>
						<tbody>
							<tr>
								<td>Technology usage gaps</td>
								<td>SO Developer Survey</td>
								<td>"Used professionally" vs "Want to learn" delta</td>
							</tr>
							<tr>
								<td>Community momentum</td>
								<td>SO public data dump</td>
								<td>Question volume, answer rates, tag velocity</td>
							</tr>
							<tr>
								<td>Ecosystem growth</td>
								<td>PyPI download stats</td>
								<td>Real adoption vs marketing noise</td>
							</tr>
							<tr>
								<td>dbt package trends</td>
								<td>dbt Hub registry</td>
								<td>Which data tools are actually growing</td>
							</tr>
						</tbody>
					</table>

					<p>Output formats are CSV, Markdown, and JSON. No paid APIs. No vendor data.</p>
				</section>

				<!-- ─── Data sources ───────────────────────────────────── -->
				<section class="content-section">
					<h2>Data sources</h2>
					<ul class="sources-list">
						<li>
							<strong>Stack Overflow Developer Survey</strong> — annual release, ~65,000 respondents.
							<a href="https://insights.stackoverflow.com/survey" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">insights.stackoverflow.com/survey ↗</a>
						</li>
						<li>
							<strong>Stack Overflow public data dump</strong> — quarterly release via SEDE and archive.org.
							<a href="https://archive.org/details/stackexchange" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">archive.org/details/stackexchange ↗</a>
						</li>
						<li>
							<strong>pypistats.org public API</strong> — 180-day rolling download window, no auth required.
							<a href="https://pypistats.org/api/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">pypistats.org/api ↗</a>
						</li>
						<li>
							<strong>dbt Hub registry</strong> — package metadata and download counts.
							<a href="https://hub.getdbt.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">hub.getdbt.com ↗</a>
						</li>
					</ul>
				</section>

				<!-- ─── Methodology ─────────────────────────────────────── -->
				<section class="content-section">
					<h2>Methodology</h2>
					<p>
						The pipeline fetches each source independently and normalizes technology names to a
						shared slug list before joining. Survey data is the anchor: every technology in the
						output must appear in at least one survey year. The hype gap is computed as
						<code>(want_to_learn_pct − used_professionally_pct)</code> per technology per survey
						year, then ranked descending. PyPI and dbt counts are joined on the slug and used as
						secondary signals to distinguish "genuinely growing" from "genuinely declining"
						regardless of survey sentiment. Refresh cadence is annual for the survey, quarterly
						for the SO dump, and on-demand for PyPI and dbt. All intermediate files are written
						to disk as CSV so any step can be rerun in isolation without re-fetching upstream
						sources.
					</p>
				</section>

				<!-- ─── Sample output ───────────────────────────────────── -->
				<section class="content-section">
					<h2>Sample output</h2>
					<p class="sample-note">Hype Gap report, truncated. Positive gap = engineers want it, companies have not adopted it. Negative gap = widely used, low desire to continue.</p>
					<pre class="sample-output"><code>Hype Gap Report — Stack Overflow Developer Survey 2024
Generated: 2024-11-03

Technology           Want (%)   Used (%)     Gap   Direction
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Rust                    29.8        8.4    +21.4   wanted
Kotlin                  26.1        9.3    +16.8   wanted
Go                      26.3       13.2    +13.1   wanted
Elixir                  11.4        3.8     +7.6   wanted
TypeScript              37.1       42.5     -5.4   regret
PHP                      8.9       19.6    -10.7   regret
COBOL                    1.2       12.4    -11.2   regret

7 of 34 technologies shown. Full output: hype_gap_2024.csv</code></pre>
				</section>

				<!-- ─── Links ────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
				<section class="content-section links-section">
					<h2>Links</h2>
					<ul class="links-list">
						<li>
							<a href="https://github.com/mryagerr/stackoverflow-monitoring" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
								Repository — github.com/mryagerr/stackoverflow-monitoring
							</a>
						</li>
						<li>
							<a href="https://github.com/mryagerr/stackoverflow-monitoring#usage" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
								Run instructions — README usage section
							</a>
						</li>
						<li>
							<a href="/about/#contact">
								Questions or feedback — contact page
							</a>
						</li>
					</ul>
					<p class="license-note">Open source, actively maintained. MIT license.</p>
				</section>

			</div>
		</main>

		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>

<style>
main {
	max-width: 860px;
	margin: 0 auto;
	padding: 3rem clamp(1.5rem, 5vw, 4rem) 4rem;
}

/* ─── Hero ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
.project-hero {
	padding-bottom: 2.5rem;
	margin-bottom: 3rem;
	border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule);
}

.breadcrumb {
	font-family: var(--font-mono);
	font-size: 0.72rem;
	font-weight: 500;
	letter-spacing: 0.06em;
	text-transform: uppercase;
	color: var(--caption);
	margin: 0 0 1.5rem;
	display: flex;
	align-items: center;
	gap: 0.5rem;
}

.breadcrumb a {
	color: var(--accent);
	text-decoration: none;
}

.breadcrumb a:hover {
	text-decoration: underline;
}

.hero-label {
	font-family: var(--font-mono);
	font-size: 0.72rem;
	font-weight: 500;
	letter-spacing: 0.14em;
	text-transform: uppercase;
	color: var(--accent);
	margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
}

.hero-title {
	font-family: var(--font-display);
	font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3rem);
	font-weight: 700;
	letter-spacing: -0.03em;
	color: var(--ink);
	margin: 0 0 1rem;
	line-height: 1.1;
}

.hero-summary {
	font-size: 1.05rem;
	line-height: 1.65;
	color: var(--caption);
	margin: 0 0 1.75rem;
	max-width: 640px;
}

.hero-meta {
	display: flex;
	align-items: center;
	flex-wrap: wrap;
	gap: 0.4rem 0.6rem;
}

.tech-tag {
	font-family: var(--font-mono);
	font-size: 0.72rem;
	font-weight: 600;
	letter-spacing: 0.04em;
	padding: 0.2em 0.7em;
	border-radius: 999px;
	background: var(--accent-muted);
	color: var(--accent-dark);
}

.meta-sep {
	color: var(--rule);
	font-size: 1.1rem;
}

.repo-link {
	font-family: var(--font-mono);
	font-size: 0.78rem;
	font-weight: 500;
	color: var(--accent);
	text-decoration: none;
	letter-spacing: 0.02em;
}

.repo-link:hover {
	color: var(--accent-dark);
	text-decoration: underline;
}

/* ─── Content sections ───────────────────────────────────────────── */
.content {
	display: flex;
	flex-direction: column;
	gap: 0;
}

.content-section {
	padding-bottom: 2.5rem;
	margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
	border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule);
}

.content-section:last-child {
	border-bottom: none;
	margin-bottom: 0;
}

.content-section h2 {
	font-family: var(--font-display);
	font-size: 1.3rem;
	font-weight: 700;
	letter-spacing: -0.02em;
	color: var(--ink);
	margin: 0 0 1rem;
}

.content-section h3 {
	font-family: var(--font-display);
	font-size: 1rem;
	font-weight: 600;
	color: var(--ink);
	margin: 1.5rem 0 0.6rem;
}

.content-section h3:first-child {
	margin-top: 0;
}

.content-section p {
	font-size: 0.95rem;
	line-height: 1.75;
	color: var(--ink);
	margin: 0 0 0.9em;
}

.content-section p:last-child {
	margin-bottom: 0;
}

.content-section code {
	font-family: var(--font-mono);
	font-size: 0.85em;
	background: rgba(var(--gray-light), 0.45);
	padding: 0.1em 0.4em;
	border-radius: 3px;
}

/* ─── Signals table ──────────────────────────────────────────────── */
.signals-table {
	width: 100%;
	border-collapse: collapse;
	font-size: 0.88rem;
	margin: 1rem 0 1.25rem;
}

.signals-table th {
	font-family: var(--font-mono);
	font-size: 0.68rem;
	font-weight: 600;
	letter-spacing: 0.08em;
	text-transform: uppercase;
	color: var(--caption);
	text-align: left;
	padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem;
	border-bottom: 2px solid var(--rule);
}

.signals-table td {
	padding: 0.6rem 0.75rem;
	border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule);
	color: var(--ink);
	line-height: 1.4;
	vertical-align: top;
}

.signals-table tr:last-child td {
	border-bottom: none;
}

.signals-table td:first-child {
	font-weight: 500;
	white-space: nowrap;
}

.signals-table td:nth-child(2) {
	font-family: var(--font-mono);
	font-size: 0.78rem;
	color: var(--caption);
	white-space: nowrap;
}

/* ─── Sources list ───────────────────────────────────────────────── */
.sources-list {
	list-style: none;
	padding: 0;
	margin: 0;
	display: flex;
	flex-direction: column;
	gap: 0.9rem;
}

.sources-list li {
	font-size: 0.92rem;
	color: var(--ink);
	line-height: 1.55;
	padding-left: 1.2rem;
	position: relative;
}

.sources-list li::before {
	content: '—';
	position: absolute;
	left: 0;
	color: var(--accent);
	font-family: var(--font-mono);
	font-size: 0.8rem;
}

.sources-list a {
	font-family: var(--font-mono);
	font-size: 0.78rem;
	color: var(--accent);
	text-decoration: none;
	display: block;
	margin-top: 0.15rem;
}

.sources-list a:hover {
	text-decoration: underline;
	color: var(--accent-dark);
}

/* ─── Sample output ──────────────────────────────────────────────── */
.sample-note {
	font-size: 0.82rem;
	color: var(--caption);
	margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
	font-style: italic;
}

.sample-output {
	margin: 0;
	padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
	background: rgba(var(--gray-light), 0.25);
	border: 1px solid var(--rule);
	border-radius: 6px;
	overflow-x: auto;
}

.sample-output code {
	font-family: var(--font-mono);
	font-size: 0.8rem;
	line-height: 1.65;
	color: var(--ink);
	background: none;
	padding: 0;
}

/* ─── Links section ──────────────────────────────────────────────── */
.links-list {
	list-style: none;
	padding: 0;
	margin: 0 0 1.25rem;
	display: flex;
	flex-direction: column;
	gap: 0.6rem;
}

.links-list li {
	padding-left: 1.2rem;
	position: relative;
}

.links-list li::before {
	content: '→';
	position: absolute;
	left: 0;
	color: var(--accent);
	font-family: var(--font-mono);
	font-size: 0.75rem;
	top: 0.15em;
}

.links-list a {
	font-size: 0.9rem;
	color: var(--accent);
	text-decoration: none;
}

.links-list a:hover {
	text-decoration: underline;
	color: var(--accent-dark);
}

.license-note {
	font-family: var(--font-mono);
	font-size: 0.75rem;
	color: var(--caption);
	letter-spacing: 0.04em;
}

/* ─── Responsive ─────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
@media (max-width: 720px) {
	.signals-table td:first-child,
	.signals-table td:nth-child(2) {
		white-space: normal;
	}
}

@media (max-width: 480px) {
	main {
		padding: 2rem 0.75rem 3rem;
	}
	.sample-output {
		padding: 1rem;
	}
	.sample-output code {
		font-size: 0.72rem;
	}
}
</style>
